## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[ ] Yes
[x] No
```

## How to Test
<!-- Add steps to run the tests suite and/or manually test -->

* Turn on the Talkback
* Navigate to call setup page
* Navigate to Join call and activate it
* Navigate to the floating header and activate participant list
* Navigate in the list with current call setting for each participant
* Observe the issue

## What to Check
Verify that the following are valid
* Participants'(currently communicating) with MIC ON visual or programmatical representation should be present.

1. When lobby overlay is showing up, ignore unexpected announcement (e.g. double tap the overlay)
2. When lobby overlay is showing up, talkback should ignore gridlayout.
3. When talkback is on and join the call, talkback should not announce "double tap" for gridlayout since the floating header is always showing up.
4. Based on E+D team's suggestion, talkback can focus on number participant on the floating header.

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
```
[ ] Yes
[X] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

```
[ ] Bugfix
[ ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[X] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## How to Test
Turn on Talkback or other screen reader
1. try to join a Teams' call -> when lobby overlay is showing up -> verify if talkback announce unexpected action "double tap" and announce unexpected info for gridlayout.
2. when join a call with talkback on, when focus on the gridlayout, verify if talkback announce unexpected "double tap" for it.

1. When lobby overlay is showing up, ignore unexpected announcement (e.g. double tap the overlay)
2. When lobby overlay is showing up, talkback should ignore gridlayout.
3. When talkback is on and join the call, talkback should not announce "double tap" for gridlayout since the floating header is always showing up.
4. Based on E+D team's suggestion, talkback can focus on number participant on the floating header.

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
```
[ ] Yes
[X] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

```
[ ] Bugfix
[ ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[X] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## How to Test
Turn on Talkback or other screen reader
1. try to join a Teams' call -> when lobby overlay is showing up -> verify if talkback announce unexpected action "double tap" and announce unexpected info for gridlayout.
2. when join a call with talkback on, when focus on the gridlayout, verify if talkback announce unexpected "double tap" for it.
3. join a call with talkback on, swipe to focus on number of participant on the floating header to verify if talkback can read it.', 'created_at': '2022-04-07T08:13:22Z', 'updated_at': The change includes:
Fix accessibility issue for mic/video/audio buttons.
Talkback can read "Join call" button on setup screen properly.
Talkback won't focus on "setup gradient" anymore.
When Talkback is on and join call, the info header will always show up on the calling screen.
Talkback won't focus on the participants number on the info header anymore.
Talkback can read audio select menu properly (includes the item position, and selected status).
When joining Team's call, when lobby overlay is up, Talkback won't focus on the switch button, info header anymore.

The change includes:
Fix accessibility issue for mic/video/audio buttons.
Talkback can read "Join call" button on setup screen properly.
Talkback won't focus on "setup gradient" anymore.
When Talkback is on and join call, the info header will always show up on the calling screen.
Talkback won't focus on the participants number on the info header anymore.
Talkback can read audio select menu properly (includes the item position, and selected status).
When joining Team's call, when lobby overlay is up, Talkback won't focus on the switch button, info header anymore.

The change includes:
Fix accessibility issue for mic/video/audio buttons.
Talkback can read "Join call" button on setup screen properly.
Talkback won't focus on "setup gradient" anymore.
When Talkback is on and join call, the info header will always show up on the calling screen.
Talkback won't focus on the participants number on the info header anymore.
Talkback can read audio select menu properly (includes the item position, and selected status).
When joining Team's call, when lobby overlay is up, Talkback won't focus on the switch button, info header anymore.

The change includes:
Fix accessibility issue for mic/video/audio buttons.
Talkback can read "Join call" button on setup screen properly.
Talkback won't focus on "setup gradient" anymore.
When Talkback is on and join call, the info header will always show up on the calling screen.
Talkback won't focus on the participants number on the info header anymore.
Talkback can read audio select menu properly (includes the item position, and selected status).
When joining Team's call, when lobby overlay is up, Talkback won't focus on the switch button, info header anymore.

When confirm leave overlay is up, Talkback should focus on the buttons on the overlay. 
When confirm leave overlay is up and swiping left or right to navigate the UI elements, Talkback should not focus on the UI elements underneath.

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
```
[ ] Yes
[X] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

```
[ ] Bugfix
[ ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[X] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## How to Test

Turn on screen reader(eg. talkback on pixel)
run the app to join group call with remote participants
using swipe to focus on leave call button on the bottom bar
double click to open confirm leave overlay
verify: 1. the first element being focused is blue button on the overlay.
            2. swiping left or right, screen reader should not focus on any UI elements under confirm leave overlay

When confirm leave overlay is up, Talkback should focus on the buttons on the overlay. 
When confirm leave overlay is up and swiping left or right to navigate the UI elements, Talkback should not focus on the UI elements underneath.

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
```
[ ] Yes
[X] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

```
[ ] Bugfix
[ ] Feature
[ ] Code style update (formatting, local variables)
[X] Refactoring (no functional changes, no api changes)
[ ] Documentation content changes
[ ] Other... Please describe:
```

## How to Test

Turn on screen reader(eg. talkback on pixel)
run the app to join group call with remote participants
using swipe to focus on leave call button on the bottom bar
double click to open confirm leave overlay
verify: 1. the first element being focused is blue button on the overlay.
            2. swiping left or right, screen reader should not focus on any UI elements under confirm leave overlay

<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Fix for crash on early back. Instead of not handling the exception (endCall called before start), we pass the error down, so it can bubble to the error handler. It now results in a prompt instead of a crash.

We might want to follow up and squash this error as well, but crash is the priority for this PR. We could return a CompletableFuture that does nothing instead of passing the error through, or we can follow up and ensure endCall() isn't called before startCall() so the condition for the error doesn't exist.

<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Fix for crash on early back. Instead of not handling the exception (endCall called before start), we pass the error down, so it can bubble to the error handler. It now results in a prompt instead of a crash.

We might want to follow up and squash this error as well, but crash is the priority for this PR. We could return a CompletableFuture that does nothing instead of passing the error through, or we can follow up and ensure endCall() isn't called before startCall() so the condition for the error doesn't exist.

## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->

## Pull Request Type

2x MeetingOptions classes no longer store Context.
Context is passed via launch() when starting the composite.

For a user, they would need to add context to Launch.

<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Potential memory leak for API User. Storing Context inside a Data object we can't guarantee where it's retained can lead to a memory leak. Passing Context in via launch is considerably safer (ensures fresh/correct context, stays a param and never a field to be leaked).


## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[X] Yes
[ ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

2x MeetingOptions classes no longer store Context.
Context is passed via launch() when starting the composite.

For a user, they would need to add context to Launch.

<!-- Describe the intention of the changes being proposed. What problem does it solve or functionality does it add? -->
* Potential memory leak for API User. Storing Context inside a Data object we can't guarantee where it's retained can lead to a memory leak. Passing Context in via launch is considerably safer (ensures fresh/correct context, stays a param and never a field to be leaked).


## Does this introduce a breaking change?
<!-- Mark one with an "x". -->
```
[X] Yes
[ ] No
```

## Pull Request Type
What kind of change does this Pull Request introduce?

2x MeetingOptions classes no longer store Context.
Context is passed via launch() when starting the composite.

For a user, they would need to add context to Launch.
